Use ternary operator to conditionally print a String if there is a boolean involved 
public class A {
    public static void main(String[] a)
    {
        String name= "Mayank";
        int age=31;
        boolean sdet=true;
        
        String role= sdet ? "SDET":"Some other role";
        
        System.out.println("Hi I am "+name+",aged "+age+" preparing for "+role);
        
    }

    
}


